v0.64.0: critters talk once evolved (speech bubbles)

- once a lineage reaches generation 4+, its mature, sufficiently-bright critters (smart species) occasionally blurt a short, spontaneous line in a speech bubble over their head
- lines come from the local LLM when AI narration is enabled (context-aware: eating / fleeing / drinking / night / hunting); otherwise a pool of cute canned lines
- sparse + brief (max 4 bubbles, ~5s each, long cooldown) so it stays fun, not spammy; new src/ui/chatter.ts + a bubble-sprite pool in the scene
- NOTE: bubbles only appear after the world evolves to gen 4+; verify in a foreground tab (background tabs throttle the sim)
